{
  "stem": "6016.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If he got some work, they-- he had to be hidden-- not to find him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But one day, after he was peddling-- tried selling little-- on the street, one day somebody knocked at the door and offered us a beautiful position, trusting us a-- a business to overtake in a country store.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was a beautiful opportunity.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But we were the only Jews there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were asked whether we would take it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my husband says, listen, the baby is small.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have time to think about this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we took-- and those were the beautiful four years of us in Cuba.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But while the first year it was so depressing, I registered for the quota to go to the United States, where my sister already was.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So during that time in Cuba, you were in Havana?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was one year in Havana and four years in the country.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were some Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And luckily, there was one from Warsaw that knew my husband's family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were some-- some survivors over there too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we talked about this, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But still not as open as-- as we would like to-- to get it out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The depression was still in there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when my daughter was born, there was a happiness-- that she will bear the name of our mothers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It happened-- my brother's name was Hannah and my husband's mother's name was Hannah.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So she was the name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was a little princess that-- that [? lifed ?] up our life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And being in a countryside where my husband was in his glory, operating a business, trusting, confidence that that was bestowed on us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was beautiful years.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then my son was born.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So again, the name of my husband's father, Simon.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
